				</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent" id="comment-4675">
				<div id="div-comment-4675" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Elisha Greenway</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-4675">January 22, 2024 at 7:41 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>Can this recipe be doubled?</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-4675" data-commentid="4675" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-4675" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Elisha Greenway" aria-label="Reply to Elisha Greenway">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				<ul class="children">
		<li class="comment byuser comment-author-dianeh bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="comment-4679">
				<div id="div-comment-4679" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Swans Down</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-4679">January 23, 2024 at 2:36 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>Hi Elisha, This recipe can definitely be doubled to make 24 cupcakes. Simply double all of the ingredients and bake according to the directions. You should not have to adjust the bake time. Happy baking!</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-4679" data-commentid="4679" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-4679" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Swans Down" aria-label="Reply to Swans Down">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1 parent" id="comment-3361">
				<div id="div-comment-3361" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Pat McDaniel</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-3361">April 2, 2023 at 12:07 am</a>		</div>

		<p>Does it matter if you use whole milk buttermilk for low fat buttermilk?</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-3361" data-commentid="3361" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-3361" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Pat McDaniel" aria-label="Reply to Pat McDaniel">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				<ul class="children">
		<li class="comment byuser comment-author-dianeh bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="comment-3366">
				<div id="div-comment-3366" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Swans Down</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-3366">April 2, 2023 at 8:01 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>Hi Pat,  You an use low-fat and whole buttermilk interchangeably without great differences in the final baked good. Happy baking!</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-3366" data-commentid="3366" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-3366" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Swans Down" aria-label="Reply to Swans Down">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent" id="comment-2567">
				<div id="div-comment-2567" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Debbie</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-2567">August 27, 2022 at 4:31 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>Tried recipe today and cupcakes came out mushy in the middle.  followed recipe exactly as written.  disappointed</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-2567" data-commentid="2567" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-2567" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Debbie" aria-label="Reply to Debbie">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				<ul class="children">
		<li class="comment byuser comment-author-dianeh bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="comment-2571">
				<div id="div-comment-2571" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Swans Down</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-2571">August 29, 2022 at 8:27 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>Hi Debbie,  We are sorry to hear that you were disappointed with the Classic Cupcake recipe.  Your information was forwarded to our Consumer Relations Department.  Someone will be reaching out.  Happy baking1</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-2571" data-commentid="2571" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-2571" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Swans Down" aria-label="Reply to Swans Down">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-2550">
				<div id="div-comment-2550" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Joyce</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-2550">July 29, 2022 at 10:36 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>I followed this recipe to the max and my cupcakes turned out delicious!!</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-2550" data-commentid="2550" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-2550" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Joyce" aria-label="Reply to Joyce">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-2534">
				<div id="div-comment-2534" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Clicquot</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-2534">July 16, 2022 at 9:36 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>This batter is SUPER loose (like alarmingly so). I went with it and was rewarded. Took exactly 23 minutes to bake (toothpick clean) and the cupcakes are light, moist and tender and perfect. Made 15 &#8220;normal size&#8221; cupcakes.</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-2534" data-commentid="2534" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-2534" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Clicquot" aria-label="Reply to Clicquot">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1 parent" id="comment-2473">
				<div id="div-comment-2473" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Karen</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-2473">May 28, 2022 at 4:27 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>Is this batter supposed to be so “soupy”</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-2473" data-commentid="2473" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-2473" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Karen" aria-label="Reply to Karen">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				<ul class="children">
		<li class="comment byuser comment-author-dianeh bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="comment-2512">
				<div id="div-comment-2512" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Swans Down</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-2512">June 30, 2022 at 9:36 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>Hi Karen,  Thanks for your feedback on the Classic Cupcake. After testing it was noted that the recipe needed adjusting.  A refreshed Classic Cupcake recipe is now in place.  Thanks and Happy Baking!</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-2512" data-commentid="2512" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-2512" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Swans Down" aria-label="Reply to Swans Down">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent" id="comment-1848">
				<div id="div-comment-1848" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Michele</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-1848">November 18, 2021 at 10:25 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>Something went wrong and I had to throw them away.  Could be operator error.  I&#8217;m going to try again, using the same flour but a different recipe.</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-1848" data-commentid="1848" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-1848" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Michele" aria-label="Reply to Michele">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				<ul class="children">
		<li class="comment byuser comment-author-dianeh bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="comment-1849">
				<div id="div-comment-1849" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Swans Down</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-1849">November 18, 2021 at 10:50 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>Hi Michelle, We&#8217;re so sorry that the recipe didn&#8217;t turn out as you had hoped.  Please come back and let us know if you have success with the second recipe. Happy Baking!</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-1849" data-commentid="1849" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-1849" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Swans Down" aria-label="Reply to Swans Down">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1 parent" id="comment-1456">
				<div id="div-comment-1456" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Monika Leftwich</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-1456">June 4, 2021 at 10:50 am</a>		</div>

		<p>Do I use salted or unsalted butter?</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-1456" data-commentid="1456" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-1456" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Monika Leftwich" aria-label="Reply to Monika Leftwich">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				<ul class="children">
		<li class="comment byuser comment-author-dianeh bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="comment-1457">
				<div id="div-comment-1457" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Swans Down</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-1457">June 4, 2021 at 3:55 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>Hi Monika,  You should use unsalted butter for the Classic Cupcake recipe.  Happy Baking!</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-1457" data-commentid="1457" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-1457" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Swans Down" aria-label="Reply to Swans Down">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent" id="comment-1138">
				<div id="div-comment-1138" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Kimberly</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-1138">January 30, 2021 at 5:15 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>What can I use instead of buttermilk</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-1138" data-commentid="1138" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-1138" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Kimberly" aria-label="Reply to Kimberly">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				<ul class="children">
		<li class="comment byuser comment-author-dianeh bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="comment-1141">
				<div id="div-comment-1141" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Swans Down</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-1141">February 1, 2021 at 2:18 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>Hi Kimberly, An easy substitution for buttermilk is; Use 1 tablespoon lemon juice or vinegar plus enough milk to make 1 cup. Let stand 5 minutes before using. Or add 1 ¾ teaspoons of cream of tartar to 1 cup whole milk.  You can find this substitution and many other useful tips on our Baking Tips page at <a href="https://swansdown.com/baking-tips/" rel="ugc">https://swansdown.com/baking-tips/</a>.  Happy baking!</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-1141" data-commentid="1141" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-1141" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Swans Down" aria-label="Reply to Swans Down">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1 parent" id="comment-1097">
				<div id="div-comment-1097" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Veruschka</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-1097">January 8, 2021 at 3:42 am</a>		</div>

		<p>Can I ask how hot does the water have to be and when should I add it in ?</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-1097" data-commentid="1097" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-1097" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Veruschka" aria-label="Reply to Veruschka">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				<ul class="children">
		<li class="comment byuser comment-author-dianeh bypostauthor odd alt depth-2" id="comment-1098">
				<div id="div-comment-1098" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Swans Down</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-1098">January 8, 2021 at 3:59 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>Hi Veruschka, The hottest that you can get from your tap, or just at boiling is ideal.  You should add it in the second step &#8220;ADD remaining ingredients.&#8221;  Happy baking!</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-1098" data-commentid="1098" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-1098" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Swans Down" aria-label="Reply to Swans Down">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li class="comment even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-780">
				<div id="div-comment-780" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Lorraine</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-780">August 15, 2020 at 2:33 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>Cupcakes were delicious. I can&#8217;t wait try the other recipes. Next time I need to make 24 cupcakes for my daughter&#8217;s birthday. I guess I will just double the recipe.</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-780" data-commentid="780" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-780" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Lorraine" aria-label="Reply to Lorraine">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li class="comment odd alt thread-even depth-1 parent" id="comment-728">
				<div id="div-comment-728" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Melernea L Neff</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-728">July 24, 2020 at 11:36 am</a>		</div>

		<p>I just made these. They are so tender and delicious. The icing is perfect. So hard to eat just two. I will be making these often.</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-728" data-commentid="728" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-728" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Melernea L Neff" aria-label="Reply to Melernea L Neff">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				<ul class="children">
		<li class="comment byuser comment-author-heatherh even depth-2" id="comment-733">
				<div id="div-comment-733" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Swans Down</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-733">July 25, 2020 at 8:45 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>Thanks Melernea, and happy baking!</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-733" data-commentid="733" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-733" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Swans Down" aria-label="Reply to Swans Down">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				</li><!-- #comment-## -->
</ul><!-- .children -->
</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-286">
				<div id="div-comment-286" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Joan Amarnani</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-286">February 21, 2020 at 6:24 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>Great flour</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-286" data-commentid="286" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-286" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Joan Amarnani" aria-label="Reply to Joan Amarnani">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-281">
				<div id="div-comment-281" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Melasia</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-281">February 3, 2020 at 11:51 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>I use these and the cupcakes where amazing ?</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-281" data-commentid="281" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-281" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Melasia" aria-label="Reply to Melasia">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-99">
				<div id="div-comment-99" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Carol Craig</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-99">July 31, 2019 at 2:57 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>wonderful recipe</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-99" data-commentid="99" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-99" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Carol Craig" aria-label="Reply to Carol Craig">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-39">
				<div id="div-comment-39" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Candy</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-39">May 13, 2019 at 8:25 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>These cupcakes were very disappointing. They turned out very &#8220;mushy,&#8221; which I attribute to the hot water. I won&#8217;t be making them again.</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-39" data-commentid="39" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-39" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Candy" aria-label="Reply to Candy">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-29">
				<div id="div-comment-29" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Larry Syverson</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-29">April 19, 2019 at 5:55 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>I have made these in the past using this recipe.. and people said they were the BEST cupcakes they have ever had.  Every bit as good as the local cupcake shop!<br />
You HAVE to use Swan&#8217;s Down cake flour or they won&#8217;t be nearly as good.  General purpose flour won&#8217;t cut it&#8230;</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-29" data-commentid="29" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-29" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Larry Syverson" aria-label="Reply to Larry Syverson">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-28">
				<div id="div-comment-28" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Larry Syverson</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-28">April 19, 2019 at 5:53 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>What would I change to make these chocolate cupcakes.. with chocolate frosting?  i.e. how much chocolate to add to the batter and frosting.</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-28" data-commentid="28" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-28" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Larry Syverson" aria-label="Reply to Larry Syverson">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li class="comment odd alt thread-odd thread-alt depth-1" id="comment-21">
				<div id="div-comment-21" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Shannon</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-21">March 23, 2019 at 3:43 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>Made this recipe and it was amazing! The cupcakes were most and light. Absolutely perfect. I received so many compliments. I will never use another recipe for cupcakes again!</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-21" data-commentid="21" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-21" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Shannon" aria-label="Reply to Shannon">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				</li><!-- #comment-## -->
		<li class="comment even thread-even depth-1" id="comment-15">
				<div id="div-comment-15" class="comment-body">
				<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<cite class="fn">Constance Campbell</cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		</div>
		
		<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
			<a href="https://swansdown.com/recipes/classic-cupcakes/#comment-15">March 8, 2019 at 3:05 pm</a>		</div>

		<p>I am making the Whipping cream pound cake  right now. This is about the 6th time I have made it. It is DELICIOUS!!</p>

		<div class="reply"><a rel="nofollow" class="comment-reply-link" href="#comment-15" data-commentid="15" data-postid="678" data-belowelement="div-comment-15" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Constance Campbell" aria-label="Reply to Constance Campbell">Reply</a></div>
				</div>
				</li><!-- #comment-## -->

            </ul>

